[1]
Date: Mon 24 Apr 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Tsatsaa via Mongolia-web.com, 24 Apr 2006 [edited]
<http://www.mongolia-web.com/content/view/417/2/>

Ulaanbaatar threatened by foot and mouth disease
------------------------------------------------
Since 1300h on Sun 23 Apr 2006, the area surrounding the Zaisan Hill in the
south of Ulaanbaatar has been quarantined. A cow belonging to the
Agricultural University died from symptoms resembling those of foot and
mouth disease [FMD]. At that time, there were 94 people in the university.
The State Veterinary Hygiene Center got a specimen from the dead cow and
determined that it was the "O" type of FMD. The Agricultural University
has, in total, 25 cattle, and the City Emergency Commission decided to cull
all of them immediately.
In the Zaisan Valley, there are 24 households with a total of 439 cattle.
There are a total of 10 pregnant women in the area that receive special
medical examination [see comment]. The Emergency commission decided to
release those people who don't live in the Valley. [A map of Mongolia can
be seen at <http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/mongolia.pdf>].
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
